A macro close-up engineering photograph capturing the detailed composite texture of an eagle-slotted vortextip deflector. The four independent curved aerodynamic trailing slats, printed out of a high-compliance flexible deep-purple thermoplastic polyurethane composite, are shown flexed under a simulated wind-tunnel shear stress load. The material highlights subtle cross-lighting along the lightening reduction slot boundaries, confirming absolute zero layer separation or stress whitening along the flex parameters, cleanroom prototype focus, photorealistic textures, 8k --ar 16:9
